<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued August 29 at 9:45PM CDT until August 29 at 10:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1015 PM CDT
FOR OCHILTREE COUNTY...
At 945 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 6 miles north of
Wolf Creek Park, or 10 miles southeast of Perryton, moving southwest
at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible. Hail
damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Perryton, Waka, Wolf Creek Park and Farnsworth.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
